13:03.199 --> 13:04.872
You know what? I know. I know you do.

13:05.118 --> 13:07.621
You know why?
Because you set the bar so high

13:07.704 --> 13:09.744
for all other women,
that no one lives up to my mom.

13:09.789 --> 13:11.257
No, it's not that.

13:11.374 --> 13:13.502
It is. I'm going to sleep, Ma. Okay?

13:13.710 --> 13:16.088
No, I... Anita says
I should tell you about

13:16.212 --> 13:18.556
the boy I fell in love with in Florida.

13:20.049 --> 13:21.089
<font color="#D900D9">(JOYCE SIGHS)</font>
- The what?

13:21.301 --> 13:23.395
It's time you know this about me, Andy.

13:23.636 --> 13:24.637
Know what?

13:24.887 --> 13:26.981
Well, there was this incident in my life

13:27.056 --> 13:29.650
that I really never told you about.

13:30.393 --> 13:31.986
I went to Florida on vacation.

13:32.061 --> 13:34.234
I was very young,
19, 20, something like that.

13:34.314 --> 13:35.315
Okay. Good.

13:35.398 --> 13:39.744
And I met a boy,
and I fell in love with him.

13:39.819 --> 13:40.945
Yeah.

13:41.404 --> 13:44.658
Honestly, Andy, I fell in love
with him kind of instantly.

13:45.116 --> 13:46.163
Okay.

13:46.242 --> 13:48.336
- He lived in Manhattan, too.
- Mmm-hmm.

13:48.411 --> 13:51.756
And so we came back and
we started seeing each other.

13:52.665 --> 13:57.091
He didn't want anything serious,
but I was just caught up with this...

13:57.337 --> 13:59.431
- Oh, the passion of it all!
- Oh.

13:59.505 --> 14:01.098
Andy, we were so passionate.

14:01.341 --> 14:04.345
Feel free to skim over those
details as much as you want.

14:04.594 --> 14:06.596
- I won't gross you out.
- Yeah. That's cool.

14:06.846 --> 14:10.771
I mean, he didn't want to be
serious, really, at the time.

14:11.017 --> 14:13.236
But I wanted a family, I wanted a baby.

14:13.311 --> 14:14.858
That's all I ever really wanted.

14:16.022 --> 14:17.774
And so, eventually,
your father came along.

14:18.024 --> 14:20.527
What about the guy from...
You met in Florida?

14:20.777 --> 14:22.495
Well, he became boyfriend number one

14:22.612 --> 14:24.410
and your dad became
boyfriend number two.

14:24.489 --> 14:25.536
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font>

14:25.615 --> 14:27.208
- No, honey...
- That's nasty!

14:27.283 --> 14:28.626
It was a trampy year for Mommy.

14:28.826 --> 14:30.578
- Oh!
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font>

14:31.287 --> 14:32.960
- Please. Anyway...
- Why are you telling me this?

14:33.122 --> 14:37.218
Your father proposed within,
like, a month, I think.

14:37.627 --> 14:39.971
So I went to the boy and I said,

14:40.296 --> 14:44.301
you know, "I met somebody
and he wants to marry me,

14:44.634 --> 14:48.980
hoping that he would say,
"Joyce, you cannot do that."

14:49.263 --> 14:50.936
"You cannot marry this guy!"

14:51.474 --> 14:54.899
But he didn't say that.
You know what he actually said?

14:55.311 --> 14:57.814
He said, "You're great."

15:00.817 --> 15:04.162
But he told me to marry your father.

15:05.279 --> 15:06.656
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES LIGHTLY)</font>

15:07.156 --> 15:08.658
Oh, God.

15:09.325 --> 15:11.168
I was so devastated.

15:12.495 --> 15:16.090
I was so devastated that
I couldn't even see him again.

15:16.332 --> 15:17.834
Well, what happened?

15:18.209 --> 15:19.426
Well...

15:19.669 --> 15:22.673
What happened?
I married your father, we moved,

15:22.922 --> 15:24.924
I got pregnant, and...

15:25.675 --> 15:29.054
When we found out
it was a boy, you know,

15:29.846 --> 15:33.851
I started going through names,
as people do, and...

15:35.017 --> 15:39.363
You want your child to remind you
of someone you love... Loved!

15:40.106 --> 15:41.449
And so...

15:42.692 --> 15:47.038
I named you Andy
after the boy from Florida.

15:52.243 --> 15:53.540
You want more ice cream?

15:56.706 --> 15:57.798
Holy shit.

15:58.040 --> 16:00.884
Andy! Please.
Enough with the language, okay?

16:01.210 --> 16:02.883
Did... Did Dad know about this?

16:03.129 --> 16:05.473
Now, that is not something
that you share

16:05.548 --> 16:06.891
with your husband. You know?

16:07.884 --> 16:09.727
Holy shit!

16:10.052 --> 16:11.349
What is wrong with you?

16:11.429 --> 16:13.477
That is enough
with the street talk, okay?

16:13.723 --> 16:14.940
Ma, I... <font color="#D900D9">(STAMMERS)</font>

16:15.475 --> 16:17.273
I need you to be honest with me, okay?

16:17.393 --> 16:18.565
Yes, I will.

16:19.562 --> 16:20.563
Is he my father?

16:20.813 --> 16:23.487
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font> No, honey.
No, he's not your father.

16:23.566 --> 16:24.658
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>
- No, no.

16:24.734 --> 16:26.828
It was two years later when I had you.

16:27.403 --> 16:29.747
His last name is Margolis.

16:31.073 --> 16:33.246
Andy Margolis.

16:33.576 --> 16:35.920
From J&R Advertising.

16:36.579 --> 16:38.297
Isn't it funny how I remember that?

16:38.414 --> 16:39.506
Yeah.

16:40.333 --> 16:41.459
Yeah.

16:51.552 --> 16:53.350
<font color="#D900D9">(DIALING)</font>

16:54.931 --> 16:56.478
<font color="#D900D9">(LINE RINGS)</font>

16:56.849 --> 16:58.192
<font color="#808080">FEMALE RECEPTIONIST:</font> <i>J&R.</i>

16:58.434 --> 17:01.062
Hi. I'm trying to track down someone

17:01.145 --> 17:03.022
who used to work
in your New York office.

17:03.105 --> 17:06.780
Probably many years ago.
The name is Andy, or...

17:07.443 --> 17:09.616
Andrew Margolis?

17:09.945 --> 17:11.289
<i>Hold on, please.</i>

17:13.281 --> 17:16.957
<i>Okay, I see that Andrew Margolis
is in our San Francisco offices.</i>

17:17.286 --> 17:21.132
Okay. Great! How long ago
did he work there?

17:21.457 --> 17:24.006
<i>No, sir. Mr. Margolis
is an Executive V.P.</i>

17:24.126 --> 17:25.844
<i>in our San Francisco office currently.</i>

17:25.962 --> 17:26.929
Really?

17:27.003 --> 17:28.631
<i>Would you like to be connected?</i>

17:28.965 --> 17:30.057
Okay!

17:30.132 --> 17:31.133
<font color="#D900D9">(LINE RINGS)</font>

17:31.217 --> 17:32.639
<font color="#808080">FEMALE ASSISTANT:</font>
Andrew Margolis's office.

17:32.885 --> 17:34.637
Seriously? No shit.

17:34.971 --> 17:38.316
Is, uh... <font color="#D900D9">(STAMMERS)</font>
Is Andrew in, please?

17:38.641 --> 17:41.235
<i>Mr. Margolis is in Europe
until next Monday.</i>

17:41.310 --> 17:42.311
<i>This is Becky.</i>

17:42.562 --> 17:45.907
Hi, Becky.
I'm a very old friend of Andrew's.

17:46.857 --> 17:51.658
We were in Nam together?

17:51.988 --> 17:53.740
Just backpacking though.

17:53.823 --> 17:56.201
And I thought it would be great
to see him again.

17:57.326 --> 17:59.670
So I guess he finally took the wife

17:59.745 --> 18:01.998
on that trip to Europe
she's always wanted, huh?

18:02.248 --> 18:04.376
<i>Mr. Margolis isn't married, sir.</i>

18:04.500 --> 18:06.753
<i>Is there a specific message
you'd like to leave?</i>

18:07.003 --> 18:09.097
No! No. So he gets back next Monday.

18:09.171 --> 18:10.172
<i>Yes, he does.</i>

18:10.506 --> 18:13.510
- Okay. Thank you.
<i>- You're welcome.</i>

18:13.718 --> 18:15.015
<font color="#D900D9">(DISCONNECTS)</font>

18:18.180 --> 18:19.853
Holy shit.

18:21.475 --> 18:23.068
I made eggs just the way you like them,

18:23.144 --> 18:24.191
and I used turkey bacon,

18:24.312 --> 18:26.815
which was on sale,
but I know it's still good.

18:27.231 --> 18:29.575
I'm always concerned
for your health, right?

18:30.568 --> 18:31.740
You know,

18:32.403 --> 18:34.952
I was up all night last night,

18:35.031 --> 18:37.409
because I was thinking
about your problems, Andy.

18:38.242 --> 18:41.416
Jessica was your first
serious relationship.

18:41.912 --> 18:43.585
So let's start with her.

18:44.081 --> 18:47.506
I remember when you broke up,
but I can't remember why.

18:47.918 --> 18:49.420
Do you remember?

18:51.881 --> 18:53.133
Hmm.

18:53.758 --> 18:56.261
Okay! We'll skip Jessica for now.

18:56.594 --> 18:58.221
Uh, what do you think
we should do today, honey?

18:58.304 --> 19:02.184
Oh, you know what? You have to
remind me to get Tylenol later,

19:02.266 --> 19:03.563
'cause I'm running low.

19:03.643 --> 19:06.692
And I also told Gayle
that I would pick some up for her.

19:06.937 --> 19:08.298
Did I remember to call Gayle back?

19:08.314 --> 19:10.783
I don't know what's happening to me.
I'm getting forgetful.

19:10.983 --> 19:12.623
You want to come
on the trip with me, Mom?

19:12.735 --> 19:14.078
Huh?

19:15.946 --> 19:19.792
My road trip, that I'm going on.
I, uh...

19:21.285 --> 19:23.458
It's long,

19:23.788 --> 19:25.961
and I thought maybe
I could use some company

19:26.040 --> 19:28.634
in the form of you.

19:31.128 --> 19:35.304
You want to drive cross-country
in a car with me?

19:38.052 --> 19:39.053
Yeah!

19:39.804 --> 19:41.806
No, it's... You know,
we won't be gone long.

19:42.056 --> 19:44.229
It's only eight days in a car together,

19:44.308 --> 19:46.857
and then I got to be in San Francisco.

19:46.936 --> 19:48.813
My last meeting's in San Francisco now.

19:49.063 --> 19:50.406
What happened to Vegas?

19:50.648 --> 19:52.328
<font color="#D900D9">(STAMMERING)</font> I got a new meeting
last night

19:52.400 --> 19:54.152
- in San Francisco, so...
- Oh.

19:54.485 --> 19:57.079
Uh... Yeah! What do you say?

19:57.154 --> 19:59.782
If this is you worrying about me, Andy,

19:59.865 --> 20:02.243
you don't have to
because Mommy's fine.

20:02.326 --> 20:04.044
That's not at all what it is, Ma.

20:04.120 --> 20:05.417
<font color="#D900D9">(STAMMERS)</font>

20:05.496 --> 20:06.497
What?

20:06.747 --> 20:08.749
I've had such a good time

20:08.999 --> 20:11.218
hanging out with you
these last few days,

20:11.293 --> 20:13.512
I thought it would be fun

20:14.004 --> 20:17.679
to hang out even more
and spend time with you.

20:18.801 --> 20:19.802
Wait a minute.

20:19.885 --> 20:23.014
I want to make sure that
I'm hearing this correctly.

20:23.681 --> 20:28.027
You want to spend a week
in a car with your mother.

20:28.686 --> 20:30.188
Is that what I heard?

20:30.688 --> 20:33.362
More than anything in the world.

20:33.691 --> 20:35.534
Don't you think I would drive you crazy?

20:35.651 --> 20:36.777
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font>

20:36.861 --> 20:39.364
Don't you think I might get
on your nerves a little bit?

20:39.613 --> 20:41.160
No, you know what?

20:41.240 --> 20:43.242
It was just a thought and
if you don't want to do it, then fine.

20:43.325 --> 20:44.406
I don't want to push you...

20:44.410 --> 20:46.458
What? What? Am I so awful
that you can't spend

20:46.537 --> 20:47.777
a little time in a car with me?

20:47.955 --> 20:49.796
Jesus Christ, Ma,
how did you turn this around?

20:49.832 --> 20:51.755
I just invited you to... I'm inviting you!

20:51.834 --> 20:54.212
Do you want to drive
across the country with me?

20:54.336 --> 20:55.679
Well, I might have to reroute my mail.

20:55.755 --> 20:56.756
Okay!

20:56.881 --> 20:58.081
I'd have to miss my book club.

20:58.340 --> 21:01.844
Ma, you have five seconds to tell me
whether you want to go or not.

21:02.094 --> 21:03.767
And then I'm revoking my offer, okay?

21:03.846 --> 21:05.063
- Are you coming?
- Okay. One, two...

21:05.181 --> 21:07.024
I can't wait! What, are you kidding me?

21:07.266 --> 21:09.143
- Honey! That is so exciting!
- Okay, great! Good! I am!

21:09.393 --> 21:12.146
- <i>Tateleh</i>! My boy, my boy!
- Okay... You really are.

21:12.229 --> 21:13.230
The sweetest...

21:13.314 --> 21:15.408
- Look at this! I love you!
- Okay, okay, easy.

21:15.733 --> 21:18.577
Oh, my God! I can't believe...
I have to call Gayle!

21:18.819 --> 21:19.911
Oh, my God!

21:19.987 --> 21:22.410
I'll have to retouch
my roots though before I go.

21:22.490 --> 21:23.491
What am I gonna pack?

21:23.574 --> 21:25.451
You've got to fill me in
on all the weather conditions

21:25.534 --> 21:27.753
in all the states
that we're gonna go through.

21:28.579 --> 21:31.753
Okay, it's fine. I got it. It's fine. I got it.

21:31.999 --> 21:33.251
Are you sure you didn't forget anything?

21:33.334 --> 21:34.506
<font color="#808080">JOYCE:</font> God, I don't know
if I forgot something.

21:34.585 --> 21:38.089
I don't think that's possible.
I may be getting a hernia.

21:38.339 --> 21:40.762
- Are you okay?
- Yeah. I'll put that here.

21:41.425 --> 21:43.098
Good, there's not
too many people here.

21:43.427 --> 21:45.771
Honey, make sure to ask
if they have any kind of deal.

21:46.096 --> 21:47.097
Okay. I will do that.

21:47.765 --> 21:49.358
Hi, I'm Mark. I'll be assisting you.

21:49.433 --> 21:50.473
Do you have a reservation?

21:50.684 --> 21:52.357
I do. Last name is Brewster.

21:52.436 --> 21:54.609
- Brewster. Okay.<font color="#808080">
ANDY:</font> - Mmm-hmm.

21:54.688 --> 21:57.032
There it is. I just need a valid
license and credit card.

21:57.274 --> 21:58.947
- Ask him.
- Okay, I will. Please relax.

21:59.193 --> 22:01.446
Please calm down, Mom!

22:01.779 --> 22:04.783
Sorry, but I just want
to confirm I got an SUV

22:04.865 --> 22:06.117
with a GPS system in it?

22:06.200 --> 22:08.544
I have you in a Dodge Durango,
GPS included,

22:08.619 --> 22:09.711
returning in San Francisco.

22:09.787 --> 22:11.255
- Great.
- Do you really need an SUV?

22:11.330 --> 22:12.957
The gas'll cost more than the car.

22:13.207 --> 22:14.709
So that comes out to $112 a day.

22:14.959 --> 22:16.802
Wait, wait, wait! I got a coupon.

22:17.044 --> 22:20.639
Good. Yeah. That works.
It takes 15% off, so...

22:21.465 --> 22:25.720
It brings your new total to $940.
Excuse me one second.

22:25.970 --> 22:27.893
- Way to go! Yeah.
- That was very exciting.

22:27.972 --> 22:29.440
- I was going to ask.
- Really.

22:29.515 --> 22:30.562
- Yes!
- I thought you forgot.

22:30.641 --> 22:33.235
You thought in the two seconds
since you reminded me...

22:33.477 --> 22:37.152
Anyway! Anyway, nowadays
small cars are fine in the snow.

22:37.398 --> 22:38.900
They probably have that GPS thing.

22:39.233 --> 22:41.327
They don't. Okay?
Only big cars have GPS.

22:41.569 --> 22:43.913
Actually, our GPS systems
are separate.

22:43.988 --> 22:45.740
You can rent them with any car.

22:45.990 --> 22:48.914
And our economy cars
handle quite well in the snow.

22:49.910 --> 22:50.911
Hmm.

22:50.995 --> 22:52.417
- Thank you, Mark.
- You're welcome.

22:52.746 --> 22:55.420
<font color="#808080">ANDY:</font> <i>So we'll just go by the circus,
drop off our clowns...</i>

22:55.666 --> 22:57.509
<font color="#808080">JOYCE:</font> <i>Andy, stop it! It's adorable.</i>

22:57.751 --> 22:59.594
<font color="#808080">ANDY:</font> <i>You sure you don't mind
driving, Ma?</i>

22:59.837 --> 23:01.464
No, honey.
You work on your presentation.

23:01.547 --> 23:02.844
I got my Book on Tape.

23:06.427 --> 23:07.428
What are you doing, Ma?

23:07.678 --> 23:09.351
Trying to find my Book on Tape.

23:09.597 --> 23:11.770
Okay. Just keep your eyes
on the road, for God sakes!

23:12.016 --> 23:14.110
- Oh, here it is.
- Okay, okay!

23:16.103 --> 23:18.856
It's called <i>Middlesex.</i>
This tape is excellent.

23:19.106 --> 23:22.030
It's about a hermaphrodite.
You know, a boy and a girl?

23:22.860 --> 23:24.533
Two different parts in one person?

23:24.778 --> 23:26.451
I... Yes, I know that.

23:26.697 --> 23:28.074
It was in Oprah's Book Club once.

23:28.240 --> 23:29.662
Say no more!

23:31.619 --> 23:33.587
<font color="#D900D9">(AUDIOBOOK PLAYING)</font>

23:35.372 --> 23:36.715
You'll like this.

23:52.848 --> 23:53.849
I love spoons.

23:56.727 --> 23:58.650
You know what? That's enough
<i>Middlesex</i> for now, I think.

23:58.896 --> 24:00.239
That's good. Yeah, we're...

24:00.481 --> 24:03.325
So, what's the plan,
my little co-captain?

24:03.567 --> 24:06.241
Well, I got three meetings today,

24:06.487 --> 24:07.830
and then I got a few in Virginia,

24:07.905 --> 24:09.498
and the last one is in Roanoke.

24:09.740 --> 24:11.083
Roanoke! Whoo!

24:11.408 --> 24:13.752
Then Texas is next. Costco. That's...

24:14.078 --> 24:16.922
That's a big one,
so if we want to get there in time,

24:16.997 --> 24:18.437
we gotta be in Tennessee by Tuesday.

24:18.666 --> 24:21.169
You know who lives
in Tennessee, right?

24:21.418 --> 24:22.510
Yes, I do. So after that...

24:22.753 --> 24:24.096
Jessica in Nashville.

24:24.213 --> 24:25.214
I know.

24:25.339 --> 24:26.761
You know, I ran into
her mother recently.

24:26.840 --> 24:28.092
She says it's lovely there!

24:28.342 --> 24:29.685
I'm sure it is. So...

24:29.885 --> 24:31.228
You know,
I spoke to Anita this morning.

24:31.428 --> 24:33.146
Anita says that it would be good for you

24:33.222 --> 24:35.441
to get some closure
with that relationship.

24:35.683 --> 24:37.936
So if we have time,
we should meet up with her.

24:38.185 --> 24:40.608
From Texas, we head to Santa Fe,

24:40.688 --> 24:42.861
where I have one more pitch,
then Vegas.

24:43.107 --> 24:45.610
Mmm! A mom and her baby boy
in Vegas. Sounds like fun!

24:45.693 --> 24:48.196
That's their new slogan,
I think, for tourism.

24:48.278 --> 24:50.406
"A mom and her baby boy
in Vegas." Yeah.

24:51.699 --> 24:52.700
Mmm.

24:52.783 --> 24:55.957
You know, I can't stop thinking about...

24:56.286 --> 24:57.287
What, honey?

24:57.538 --> 24:59.381
About that story you told me
the other night, honestly.

24:59.456 --> 25:00.548
About Andy Margolis.

25:00.791 --> 25:03.419
I mean, tell me more about him.
What was it...

25:03.502 --> 25:05.262
What was it about him
that you liked so much?

25:06.130 --> 25:07.382
I don't know.

25:07.631 --> 25:10.134
Broad shoulders, you know.
Oops! Sorry.

25:10.467 --> 25:14.313
Okay, what else?
Anything less physically based?

25:15.973 --> 25:17.725
I was cross-eyed when I was a little girl.

25:17.808 --> 25:18.809
I told you that, right?

25:19.059 --> 25:21.562
What does this have to do
with what I asked you?

25:21.812 --> 25:25.066
Well, one day I meet this boy,
out of nowhere.

25:25.399 --> 25:28.699
Andy Margolis.
We went out on this first date.

25:29.153 --> 25:33.499
We were dancing,
and he told me that I was beautiful.

25:35.242 --> 25:38.587
He was the first person
to ever tell me that.

25:43.500 --> 25:45.252
Don't you ever wonder, like, where he is,

25:45.335 --> 25:46.336
what happened to him?

25:46.670 --> 25:47.922
A little bit?

25:48.505 --> 25:51.850
It's in the past, Andy. It's in the past.

25:55.345 --> 25:58.019
<font color="#808080">ANDY:</font> <i>I could probably
find him if you really wanted.</i>

25:58.265 --> 25:59.858
<font color="#808080">JOYCE:</font> <i>Don't you dare!</i>

25:59.933 --> 26:01.685
<i>He's probably fat
and obnoxious by now.</i>

26:01.852 --> 26:03.149
<font color="#808080">ANDY:</font> <i>Maybe he's just fat.</i>

26:04.605 --> 26:06.357
<font color="#D900D9">(INDISTINCT CHATTING)</font>

26:09.276 --> 26:11.904
What are you doing? No, no!
Don't move their stuff around!

26:11.987 --> 26:14.206
What are you doing?
Just put it on the floor.

26:14.323 --> 26:16.576
