- Put your hood up, honey.
- No. I don't want to.

38:31.976 --> 38:34.525
Oh. Here it is.

38:34.854 --> 38:37.528
You got ice frozen up around the tire.

38:37.732 --> 38:40.531
It's blocking the wheel and making it
feel like you got a flat.

38:40.652 --> 38:41.653
- My God!
- You sure about that?

38:41.736 --> 38:42.737
You sure it's not flat?

38:43.029 --> 38:44.372
I'm positive.

38:46.032 --> 38:47.875
Wow! She really is a mechanic!

38:48.076 --> 38:49.578
She really knows what she's doing.

38:49.702 --> 38:51.420
My God, you weren't kidding.

38:51.579 --> 38:52.922
Thank you very much.

38:53.206 --> 38:55.007
Those heels come in handy.
I'm very impressed.

38:56.042 --> 38:58.841
May I interest you in a private dance?

38:58.920 --> 39:00.843
Oh! I'd love... Thank you,

39:00.922 --> 39:03.846
but maybe another time
when my mom's not here.

39:03.925 --> 39:05.427
On! <font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font>

39:05.552 --> 39:07.225
- Great. Thank you.
- Okay.

39:07.303 --> 39:08.475
God bless, y'all!

39:08.596 --> 39:10.690
- Bye bye! Cover up!
- Oh, thank you, Miss Joyce.

39:10.765 --> 39:13.268
They're saying you shouldn't
get on the highway right now.

39:13.393 --> 39:14.440
Are you staying local?

39:14.727 --> 39:16.727
Yeah, we'll just get
a hotel or something, I guess.

39:17.063 --> 39:19.236
Well, actually,
we don't have to because...

39:19.566 --> 39:21.113
It's gonna be tough finding
a room anywhere in this.

39:21.234 --> 39:22.201
I bet.

39:22.277 --> 39:23.620
You got anywhere you can crash?

39:23.695 --> 39:25.948
- Yeah!
- No. We do not.

39:26.239 --> 39:28.241
- We do know somebody.
- We don't.

39:28.658 --> 39:30.178
- Don't you think we...
- No, we don't.

39:30.577 --> 39:32.420
<font color="#808080">JOYCE:</font> We could call... You know.

39:32.537 --> 39:34.790
<i>Jessica, thanks
for picking us up, honey.</i>

39:35.248 --> 39:36.750
Your mother fills me in occasionally.

39:36.958 --> 39:38.926
How have you been, honey?

39:39.419 --> 39:42.093
- Uh, well, pregnant, Mrs. B.
<font color="#D900D9">(BOTH LAUGH)</font>

39:42.589 --> 39:46.014
Yeah, I'm due again in April.
I feel like a house.

39:46.301 --> 39:47.803
Oh, no. Well, you look fantastic!

39:48.094 --> 39:49.311
Yeah. You look very pretty, still.

39:49.429 --> 39:50.646
Oh, well, thank you. I...

39:51.431 --> 39:52.774
I appreciate the lie.

39:52.891 --> 39:54.393
No, not a lie at all.

39:55.435 --> 39:57.608
Honestly, I don't know
how I keep getting pregnant.

39:57.687 --> 39:59.109
<font color="#808080">ROB:</font> I got a theory.

39:59.188 --> 40:01.156
It's called two margaritas
and <i>Love Actually.</i>

40:01.232 --> 40:02.734
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL LAUGH)</font>

40:02.817 --> 40:04.114
<font color="#808080">ANDY:</font> Every time, right?

40:06.279 --> 40:07.326
<font color="#808080">JOYCE:</font> Very nice house!

40:07.447 --> 40:09.449
Yeah. Very lovely color. Good paint job.

40:09.782 --> 40:12.456
- New paint job, new fixtures.
- It's very beautifully done.

40:12.785 --> 40:14.537
It's quite a setup you have here.

40:14.621 --> 40:15.622
Well, thanks.

40:16.122 --> 40:17.624
Yeah, we like it.

40:17.790 --> 40:20.168
I think it took a while
for my Jersey girl here

40:20.251 --> 40:22.128
to get adjusted, but I think she digs it.

40:22.503 --> 40:23.675
<font color="#808080">JESSICA:</font> Yeah, I do.

40:23.755 --> 40:25.598
So, wait... So, Andy, you and Jessica

40:25.673 --> 40:26.970
were high school sweethearts?

40:27.050 --> 40:29.348
Yeah, we dated for a while
in high school. Yeah.

40:29.594 --> 40:31.312
It was great. It was a really fun time.

40:31.638 --> 40:33.515
Oh, wow. Hey, you know,
she talks about you all the time.

40:33.848 --> 40:35.725
- Oh!
- Really? That's funny,

40:35.808 --> 40:37.856
because we've been talking
about Jessica a lot.

40:38.144 --> 40:41.273
I don't know if we
talk about her a lot. Have we?

40:41.356 --> 40:43.154
I mean, a normal amount.

40:43.483 --> 40:45.281
She came up several times
in conversation.

40:45.526 --> 40:47.494
<font color="#808080">ANDY:</font> - Very casually.
- You see, Jessica,

40:47.987 --> 40:51.992
Andy is still single,
and we were wondering whether

40:52.200 --> 40:55.374
your break-up had anything to
do with it. What do you think?

40:55.453 --> 40:58.798
No, yeah, don't be ridiculous.
I mean, we were just kids.

40:59.332 --> 41:01.710
You broke up with me
when we were, what, like, 17?

41:01.876 --> 41:02.968
- Eighteen.
- Eighteen.

41:03.044 --> 41:04.546
<font color="#808080">ANDY:</font> Mmm-hmm.<font color="#808080">
JOYCE:</font> Wait a minute.

41:05.505 --> 41:07.507
You broke up with her?

41:08.174 --> 41:09.847
Well, technically, I guess.

41:10.051 --> 41:11.553
God! Remember how crazy you were?

41:11.719 --> 41:13.813
I was young and kind of...

41:13.888 --> 41:16.016
You know, I felt a lot. Big feelings.

41:16.224 --> 41:18.477
Mrs. B, did you know that
Andy proposed to me

41:18.559 --> 41:19.902
right before we went to college?

41:20.186 --> 41:22.735
It was like a serious
get-on-your-knee kind of proposal

41:22.814 --> 41:24.494
right in the middle of the football field.

41:24.691 --> 41:26.739
It was silly. It was a silly thing to do.

41:26.943 --> 41:29.867
I said we were too young,
obviously, and he ended it,

41:29.946 --> 41:31.118
just like that!

41:31.197 --> 41:32.323
Mmm-hmm.

41:32.907 --> 41:33.908
Yeah!

41:34.075 --> 41:35.595
Andy, can you imagine if I'd said yes?

41:35.743 --> 41:36.960
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

41:37.704 --> 41:39.047
No.

41:39.539 --> 41:40.916
<font color="#808080">JESSICA:</font> Hmm.

41:51.759 --> 41:53.136
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

41:55.555 --> 41:58.559
You proposed to her. Andy, that's so...

42:00.476 --> 42:01.819
I wish I knew that.

42:03.563 --> 42:06.066
Well, you do now.

42:11.070 --> 42:13.072
I was just trying to help.

42:13.948 --> 42:15.165
You always are.

42:17.618 --> 42:20.292
Maybe it was healthy to see her.

42:21.247 --> 42:23.124
Maybe it'll help you get on with your life.

42:24.417 --> 42:27.921
Or maybe, just once, you could have,

42:28.963 --> 42:31.307
one time, just minded
your own business, Ma.

42:31.382 --> 42:32.622
Maybe that could have happened.

42:33.760 --> 42:36.263
Look, I have Costco today, okay?

42:36.596 --> 42:37.643
I would appreciate it very much

42:37.764 --> 42:40.517
if we could just drive in
silence until we get to Texas.

42:40.600 --> 42:41.601
I would...

42:42.935 --> 42:44.778
I would appreciate that very much.

42:55.406 --> 42:56.407
<font color="#D900D9">(CLEARS THROAT)</font>

43:06.834 --> 43:08.928
<font color="#D900D9">(MUTTERING)</font>

43:18.471 --> 43:20.348
They're gonna come
get me in a second,

43:20.431 --> 43:23.150
so just wait here until I'm
back and don't talk to anyone.

43:23.643 --> 43:25.987
- Can I just say one thing?
- No. You can't.

43:26.312 --> 43:28.113
Andy, I don't think
they're coming to get you.

43:28.856 --> 43:30.278
Why would they not
be coming down to get me?

43:30.358 --> 43:31.735
Because I'm noticing
how it's done here.

43:31.901 --> 43:33.494
It's like a different thing. You know?

43:33.569 --> 43:35.446
They come to your table or something.

43:35.530 --> 43:38.454
The people with the red,
they see things on the table.

43:38.533 --> 43:40.206
You bring your product or something. I...

43:40.326 --> 43:41.498
Shit!

43:41.702 --> 43:44.205
- Go away. Just leave.
- Where am I gonna meet you?

43:44.497 --> 43:46.499
- Andrew?
- Hi! Hi there!

43:46.833 --> 43:49.882
A pleasure to finally meet you, Andrew.
Ryan McFee.

43:50.503 --> 43:51.846
- Yeah. Great.
- Costco.

43:52.046 --> 43:54.390
This is Joyce. Joyce...

43:55.007 --> 43:57.009
...-ton, my... Joyce Joyston.

43:57.343 --> 43:59.266
<font color="#D900D9">(STAMMERING)</font> My business partner.

43:59.345 --> 44:00.312
- Ah!
- Yes!

44:00.388 --> 44:01.389
I'm his business partner.

44:01.514 --> 44:03.608
- Then you should have a seat.
- Fantastic! Yeah!

44:03.683 --> 44:05.856
- Of course. Have a seat.
- "Business partner, sit!"

44:05.935 --> 44:07.733
<font color="#808080">ANDY:</font> Yes. Why wouldn't you?

44:07.812 --> 44:10.861
So, I would just like
to start by saying how

44:11.190 --> 44:13.659
honored I am that Costco Wholesale
would meet with me.

44:13.734 --> 44:16.203
I know the backing of Costco

44:16.279 --> 44:19.374
could really make a product
into something big.

44:19.448 --> 44:20.700
Well, I'm looking forward
to hearing your pitch.

44:20.783 --> 44:21.784
Thank you.

44:21.909 --> 44:24.253
Now, some history on my product.

44:24.745 --> 44:26.372
- I'm sorry.
- No problem!

44:26.873 --> 44:28.875
- What is that?
- My purse hook.

44:29.167 --> 44:30.168
What does it do?

44:30.376 --> 44:34.677
It just keeps the pocketbook
from touching the dirty floor.

44:34.755 --> 44:36.098
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font>

44:36.382 --> 44:39.682
- Ah! That is great!
- Yeah, it's really neat.

44:39.927 --> 44:41.929
Where'd you get that, the purse hook?

44:42.138 --> 44:43.640
Uh, Amazon, I think.

44:45.016 --> 44:46.233
Hmm.

44:50.271 --> 44:52.820
<font color="#D900D9">(MOUTHING)</font>

44:52.899 --> 44:54.242
<font color="#D900D9">(WHISPERING)</font> GO.

44:54.442 --> 44:56.365
<font color="#D900D9">(WHISPERING)</font> No, I am not going.
It's rude.

44:57.570 --> 44:58.913
- Go.
- No, it would look bad.

44:59.113 --> 45:00.114
Get out of here!

45:00.281 --> 45:03.080
It's very rude. Extremely rude.

45:03.284 --> 45:04.627
Will you just go?

45:04.911 --> 45:05.912
Stop that.

45:06.120 --> 45:07.918
Sorry. Please, continue.

45:08.915 --> 45:12.590
I created a micro-emulsion
suspension, Ryan,

45:12.919 --> 45:17.925
that harnesses the natural
cleaning and foaming power of

45:18.174 --> 45:19.676
coconut oil,

45:20.885 --> 45:22.228
palm kernel oil...

45:23.095 --> 45:24.096
Oxygen.

45:24.305 --> 45:25.306
...and

45:26.265 --> 45:27.608
soy!

45:27.934 --> 45:29.902
Or as I like to call it,

45:30.603 --> 45:32.446
- Scieoclean!
- Scieoclean!

45:33.272 --> 45:34.444
Sounds good.

45:34.857 --> 45:36.279
Oh, Oh!

45:37.276 --> 45:40.155
Scieoclean. Yes.
It took me a second. Sorry.

45:40.446 --> 45:44.326
It read at first like Skyoclean.
Or Psychoclean.

45:44.617 --> 45:45.994
That's an unusual response.

45:46.285 --> 45:48.629
Don't get hung up on the name, Ryan.

45:48.829 --> 45:52.834
I mean, because Andrew
was thinking of changing it.

45:53.125 --> 45:55.219
<font color="#808080">RYAN:</font> - Oh, that's a good idea.
- Is he? Ah.

45:55.670 --> 45:57.672
- Joyce is right. It's unclear.<font color="#808080">
JOYCE:</font> - Uh-huh. I agree.

45:57.755 --> 45:59.098
Yeah. I wasn't really considering it.

45:59.173 --> 46:00.140
I don't know what...

46:00.216 --> 46:02.093
- We talked about changing it.
- No, we didn't.

46:02.176 --> 46:03.428
- In the hotel.
- I don't remember that.

46:03.511 --> 46:05.229
You said that
the other night at the hotel.

46:05.346 --> 46:06.347
- I did?
- Don't you remember, honey?

46:06.514 --> 46:07.936
- Don't call me "honey."
- Mr. Brewster.

46:08.015 --> 46:12.612
Maybe if you simply relabeled
the bottle "Science Clean."

46:13.521 --> 46:14.773
That's a good idea.

46:14.855 --> 46:17.016
I don't actually have any
money to relabel any bottles.

46:17.024 --> 46:18.504
Wait a minute. How much would it cost

46:18.526 --> 46:19.527
to relabel the bottles?

46:19.652 --> 46:21.199
Bulk? <font color="#D900D9">(SCOFFS)</font>
A fraction of a cent.

46:21.654 --> 46:23.334
Half a cent!
And you're going to sell bulk.

46:23.531 --> 46:24.532
What's the big deal?

46:24.657 --> 46:26.204
Well, the aggregate amount...

46:26.284 --> 46:27.957
So, listen, Andrew,
when you relabel the bottle...

46:28.077 --> 46:29.078
"When" is a little preemptive.

46:29.203 --> 46:31.626
I don't know if I would jump
to the "when" conclusion.

46:31.706 --> 46:33.879
- Listen to what he's saying.
- When you do, I would change

46:33.958 --> 46:35.210
- the whole color scheme.
- I agree.

46:35.293 --> 46:37.421
It should be more, like, magenta.

46:37.586 --> 46:38.929
What's gonna pop? You know?

46:39.005 --> 46:41.804
I would strongly consider
relabeling that bottle.

46:41.882 --> 46:43.555
I know, but I put
a lot of thought into this...

46:43.634 --> 46:45.307
<font color="#808080">JOYCE:</font> Listen to what
the man is saying.

46:45.386 --> 46:46.808
<font color="#808080">RYAN:</font> You're going to have
to relabel the bottle.

46:47.054 --> 46:49.728
I'm not changing
the goddamn label, Ryan!

46:54.145 --> 46:55.488
Okay.

47:03.821 --> 47:06.074
I know. I shouldn't have said anything.

47:06.824 --> 47:08.167
Yep.

47:10.328 --> 47:13.172
There are many other stores
besides Costco.

47:14.165 --> 47:15.337
Yep.

47:15.666 --> 47:18.340
Think of all the other sales
you already made.

47:31.932 --> 47:33.184
Ah!

47:36.103 --> 47:37.229
Well, the good news is,

47:37.313 --> 47:39.941
I have got enough hair product
to last me for years.

47:45.905 --> 47:47.282
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

47:49.450 --> 47:51.828
if you're going to drink all that alcohol,

47:51.952 --> 47:54.125
you should really hydrate.

48:02.963 --> 48:05.466
I don't want to say it again, so...

48:05.966 --> 48:09.641
So, I'll just leave the water bottle here.

48:15.142 --> 48:18.316
I only say that because

48:18.646 --> 48:21.445
I read that for every glass
of alcohol that you drink,

48:21.524 --> 48:23.492
you need an extra glass of water...

48:23.984 --> 48:25.657
Ma. Ma!

48:27.154 --> 48:31.125
Can you not see that I don't
want to talk right now?

48:31.200 --> 48:32.793
Are you... Are you blind?

48:33.160 --> 48:34.833
How idiotic can you be?

48:34.954 --> 48:38.003
Can you not tell
that I don't want any water?

48:38.332 --> 48:41.927
Enough with the nagging
and the water! Just shut up!

48:42.378 --> 48:44.221
Just shut up!

48:52.513 --> 48:54.356
I don't know what to say.

48:55.975 --> 48:56.976
Finally.

48:57.852 --> 48:58.853
"Finally", you said?

49:04.024 --> 49:05.867
You little shit.

49:06.360 --> 49:07.486
Mmm!

49:08.028 --> 49:12.329
You condescending,
self-absorbed little shit.

49:14.076 --> 49:16.795
I can't do anything right
by you, can I, Andy?

49:18.038 --> 49:21.383
Everything I say is wrong,
everything I do is wrong.

49:23.210 --> 49:25.838
Go ahead. Why don't you
keep insulting me?

49:26.714 --> 49:28.387
'Cause you haven't made it quite clear

49:28.507 --> 49:31.727
just how much
you can't stand being with me!

49:32.887 --> 49:35.982
What do you think, I'm stupid?
You think I'm stupid?

49:36.557 --> 49:40.528
No. You think I don't know that
you went to school in California

49:40.895 --> 49:43.239
so that you'd only
have to see me once a year?

49:44.231 --> 49:45.403
Why, Andy? Why?

49:45.774 --> 49:47.617
What did I do wrong?

49:48.402 --> 49:50.530
What did I do?
Did I care for you too much?

49:50.613 --> 49:53.036
Did I love you too much? What did I do?

49:53.449 --> 49:55.668
- Okay, Ma.
- It's not okay!

49:55.910 --> 49:57.503
This is the way you talk to me?

49:57.745 --> 50:01.340
Like I'm some thing that
has to be tolerated?

50:01.916 --> 50:04.089
Well, let me tell you something, kiddo.

50:04.418 --> 50:07.592
You don't have to like me,
or spend time with me.

50:07.963 --> 50:09.761
But as long as I'm your mother,

50:09.882 --> 50:11.555
you will treat me with respect.

50:12.092 --> 50:13.514
Now drink your fucking water

50:13.594 --> 50:16.393
before you drop dead from dehydration!

50:19.892 --> 50:20.893
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

50:21.435 --> 50:22.778
<font color="#D900D9">(DOOR BANGS SHUT)</font>

50:26.273 --> 50:28.071
<font color="#D900D9">(INDISTINCT)</font>

50:49.672 --> 50:50.969
<font color="#D900D9">(BELL TINKLING)</font>

50:53.133 --> 50:55.135
<font color="#808080">JOYCE:</font> I was telling you this story

50:55.219 --> 50:56.812
that was about Macy's and...

50:56.887 --> 50:58.889
- You heard of Macy's?<font color="#808080">
JIMMY:</font> - Yes, ma'am.

50:59.139 --> 51:00.937
<font color="#808080">JOYCE:</font> I was sitting in the car, you see,

51:01.016 --> 51:03.565
and I was trying to jam
the key in the ignition,

51:03.644 --> 51:06.363
but it wouldn't turn on.
And you know why it wouldn't turn on?

51:06.480 --> 51:08.482
Because I was sitting in the wrong car!

51:08.566 --> 51:09.567
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL LAUGHING)</font>

51:09.650 --> 51:13.154
Isn't that funny?
It was very funny at the time.

51:13.320 --> 51:15.869
- Hey, Ma.
- Oh, my God!

51:16.156 --> 51:19.160
Look at who's here. The big, bad son!

51:19.493 --> 51:21.495
- Andy!<font color="#808080">
MAN:</font> - Hey, son.

51:21.704 --> 51:23.047
What, did you come to get me?

51:23.247 --> 51:25.408
We should probably head back
to the room, for a minute.

51:25.416 --> 51:26.918
- I don't think so.
- No?

51:27.001 --> 51:29.754
I'm having fun here, Andy!
I'm being fun!

51:30.004 --> 51:32.006
And I'm meeting men! Andy!

51:32.214 --> 51:33.466
Isn't that what you wanted?

51:33.549 --> 51:34.675
That's not really what I meant, Mom.

51:34.758 --> 51:37.181
Everybody, say hello to my little boy

51:37.428 --> 51:41.023
who lives in California,
far away from his mommy.

51:41.265 --> 51:42.733
The opposite side of the world.

51:43.350 --> 51:45.444
- Ma, you're drunk right now.
- Please!

51:45.519 --> 51:46.736
- You've had too much to drink.
- I am not drunk.

51:46.937 --> 51:49.110
I'm not drunk! He's far, far away.

51:49.356 --> 51:51.529
But that's okay! It's okay. Jimmy?

51:51.775 --> 51:55.450
You know it's okay because
he calls me on my birthday

51:55.696 --> 51:57.790
and sometimes he comes home
for Thanksgiving.

51:58.032 --> 52:01.377
I need another one
of these drinky-poos! Okay?

52:01.452 --> 52:02.624
Coming up.

52:02.870 --> 52:04.622
Jimmy, I think she's actually
had enough to drink,

52:04.705 --> 52:05.706
thank you very much.

52:06.040 --> 52:08.543
No, I haven't!
Don't listen to him, Jimmy!

52:08.876 --> 52:11.550
I want another drink,
and I need more cheesy fries.

52:13.047 --> 52:16.221
Seriously, I think
she's had enough to drink.

52:16.550 --> 52:17.802
Sorry, boss.

52:17.885 --> 52:19.686
The lady wants a drink,
she's getting a drink.

52:19.887 --> 52:23.733
The thing is, the lady doesn't
actually need a drink.

52:24.058 --> 52:25.401
I paid for it, she's drinking it.

52:25.643 --> 52:27.896
Look, you are crazy if you think

52:27.978 --> 52:29.901
I'm gonna let you
give that drink to my mom.

52:30.147 --> 52:31.865
You should just get out of my way now.

52:31.940 --> 52:32.941
Wait...

52:33.734 --> 52:36.078
Actually, I'm really tired.

52:36.403 --> 52:38.906
I think we should be going.
We gotta be going.

52:38.989 --> 52:40.912
No, no, no, no, no.

52:41.075 --> 52:42.292
- Thank you so much.
- Joyce...

52:42.743 --> 52:44.120
- No...
- Hey! Hey!

52:45.579 --> 52:46.922
<font color="#808080">JOYCE:</font> Oh, my God!

52:47.581 --> 52:48.924
No, no, Jimmy...

52:48.999 --> 52:50.376
<font color="#D900D9">(ANDY GROANS)</font>

53:03.931 --> 53:05.433
Quite a night.

53:11.772 --> 53:13.133
Do you remember what I used to say

53:13.190 --> 53:15.864
when people asked me what
I wanted to be when I grew up?

53:19.113 --> 53:21.957
I didn't say baseball player.

53:22.282 --> 53:24.330
A lot of my friends
wanted to be Power Rangers.

53:24.451 --> 53:26.624
That was a very popular profession.

53:27.204 --> 53:28.644
I was the weirdest kid in the world,

53:28.664 --> 53:31.543
because I said organic chemist
every time!

53:31.792 --> 53:34.796
I mean, that's the only thing
I ever wanted to be.

53:35.129 --> 53:36.472
Do you remember that?

53:36.797 --> 53:38.219
Yes, I do.

53:39.299 --> 53:42.143
Always doing these strange

53:42.469 --> 53:44.972
experiments in the basement,

53:45.305 --> 53:48.479
wearing these goggles.
I remember them.

53:48.726 --> 53:50.728
Four times too big for your head.

53:50.978 --> 53:53.652
Dude, those things
saved my eyes many times.

53:58.318 --> 54:02.994
I went to UCLA because they have
the best organic chemistry program

54:03.323 --> 54:04.825
in the country.

54:05.659 --> 54:07.002
That's the only reason.

54:25.387 --> 54:26.730
You hungry?

54:28.056 --> 54:29.774
- Always.
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font> Okay.

54:32.394 --> 54:34.067
<font color="#808080">JOYCE:</font> All right. Let's see.

54:35.397 --> 54:37.070
I'll have an appetizer...

54:38.400 --> 54:39.401
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

54:39.485 --> 54:40.486
Thanks.

54:41.320 --> 54:42.663
I like those hats.

54:46.408 --> 54:48.706
I'm sorry about last night,
Ma, what I said.

54:48.786 --> 54:51.255
I shouldn't have said that.

54:51.914 --> 54:53.257
I said some things, too.

54:53.373 --> 54:54.374
Yeah, you did.

54:54.750 --> 54:55.876
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

54:59.421 --> 55:01.264
I haven't made one sale, Ma.

55:02.466 --> 55:03.467
I, uh...

55:04.760 --> 55:07.934
I've spent the last five years
developing a product

55:08.013 --> 55:09.356
that's really good,

55:09.431 --> 55:12.184
and that I can't sell, at all, to anybody.

55:12.434 --> 55:15.608
All my money, all my time,
all the money Dad left me,

55:15.854 --> 55:18.198
I have none of that anymore.

55:18.440 --> 55:20.283
And, honestly, I have

55:20.609 --> 55:24.284
no idea what I'm going to do
from now on, so...

55:24.947 --> 55:26.369
I thought you should know that.

55:27.282 --> 55:29.956
- Why didn't you say anything?
- I don't know.

55:30.285 --> 55:33.710
You know, you always say,
"Who could say no to you?"

55:33.789 --> 55:34.790
I didn't want to...

55:35.374 --> 55:37.376
I didn't want to have to read you the list.

55:41.255 --> 55:42.598
I could give you advice.

55:42.798 --> 55:45.642
- I'm sure you could.
- But I'm not going to.

55:46.134 --> 55:49.138
'Cause you're a grown-up, Andy,

55:49.471 --> 55:52.816
and I want you to be your own man.

55:53.058 --> 55:55.402
- So you can...
- When did you call Anita?

55:56.645 --> 55:58.818
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLING)</font> Before I went
to the bar last night.

55:58.897 --> 56:00.365
Okay. <font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font>

56:00.566 --> 56:02.364
Andy, don't give up, okay?

56:02.442 --> 56:04.410
I mean, we still have
three more meetings, right?

56:04.653 --> 56:07.827
We have Santa Fe,
we have Vegas, San Francisco.

56:08.156 --> 56:10.659
- And it's not over yet, okay?
- Um...

56:13.161 --> 56:14.287
Yeah.

56:15.497 --> 56:17.340
About San Francisco, Ma...

56:17.583 --> 56:19.503
Welcome to Cattlemen's.
Y'all know what you want?

56:19.585 --> 56:21.679
What is this... What is this thing here?

56:21.920 --> 56:23.422
Oh, that's our specialty!

56:23.505 --> 56:25.599
It's the biggest piece
of Grade A steak around.

56:25.841 --> 56:27.343
- Yeah?
- Fifty ounces!

56:27.843 --> 56:30.266
It comes with a dinner salad, roll,

56:30.345 --> 56:32.439
shrimp cocktail and a baked potato.

56:32.681 --> 56:34.558
Now, if you can eat that all
in under an hour,

56:34.641 --> 56:36.769
you get it for free. And you get a T-shirt!

56:37.019 --> 56:40.193
Really? How much is it
if you don't finish?

56:40.439 --> 56:41.611
A hundred bucks.

56:41.857 --> 56:43.017
- A hundred bucks?
- Whoa, Ma,

56:43.025 --> 56:44.368
are you kidding me right now?

56:44.610 --> 56:47.159
You're broke, honey.
Don't turn free down.

56:47.237 --> 56:48.534
And you know how I can eat!

56:48.780 --> 56:51.374
Yeah, that's four and a half
pounds of meat, Mom.

56:51.450 --> 56:53.202
That's a lot of meat!

56:53.452 --> 56:55.875
I mean, that's like eating
a poodle. You know?

56:55.954 --> 56:57.354
You actually think you can do that?

56:57.372 --> 57:00.091
I don't just think it, honey. I know it.

57:00.167 --> 57:02.044
It's just if I want to do it, that's it.

57:02.377 --> 57:03.799
Well, you want to do it, hon?

57:05.631 --> 57:07.633
Yeah. I'm gonna do it.

57:07.716 --> 57:09.639
But I want the salad dressing
on the side.

57:10.385 --> 57:11.637
It's a Weight Watchers thing.

57:11.720 --> 57:12.892
Ladies and gentlemen!
<font color="#D900D9">(BANGS ON TABLE)</font>

57:12.971 --> 57:15.520
If you would direct
your attention to the stage,

57:15.599 --> 57:17.522
you will find Miss Joyce Brewster.

57:17.601 --> 57:19.148
- Hi.
<font color="#D900D9">(APPLAUSE)</font>

57:20.228 --> 57:21.428
Now, Joyce is from New Jersey.

57:21.438 --> 57:22.485
<font color="#D900D9">(CROWD BOOING)</font>

57:22.564 --> 57:24.157
- Hey, now...
- Oh, that's not nice.

57:24.232 --> 57:26.576
That's not nice!
Joyce is from New Jersey,

57:26.652 --> 57:28.996
but she's going to eat
like a Texan tonight!

57:29.071 --> 57:30.618
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL CHEERING)</font>

57:32.407 --> 57:34.751
Now, in the next hour,
Joyce will have to consume

57:34.826 --> 57:36.749
a tossed salad,
with dressing on the side...

57:36.995 --> 57:37.996
Healthy.

57:38.246 --> 57:40.419
One of our dinner rolls.

57:40.874 --> 57:41.841
Yum!

57:41.917 --> 57:43.590
A shrimp cocktail!

57:44.252 --> 57:46.596
- Love them.
- A baked potato!

57:48.256 --> 57:50.930
As well as this here.

57:51.051 --> 57:52.268
<font color="#D900D9">(CROWD EXCLAIMING)</font>

57:53.428 --> 57:55.430
Wow! That is big!

57:55.847 --> 57:57.190
Holy shit!

57:57.265 --> 57:59.768
And it all has to get down and stay down
in under an hour.

57:59.935 --> 58:02.438
Everybody, let's give Joyce
a great big hand!

58:02.521 --> 58:03.818
<font color="#D900D9">(CHEERING)</font>

58:07.609 --> 58:09.282
- And let's go!
- Okay.

58:09.611 --> 58:12.455
- I have to put my napkin down.
- Come on, Joyce!

58:15.617 --> 58:16.994
Don't get all dainty, Joyce.

58:17.077 --> 58:18.624
- Just dig in. Like a buzz saw.
- Okay.

58:18.954 --> 58:20.922
All right, thank you. Okay.

58:21.456 --> 58:22.628
Whoa, this is thick.

58:22.874 --> 58:24.394
- Just eat it.<font color="#808080">
JOYCE:</font> - My first bite!

58:27.337 --> 58:28.554
<font color="#D900D9">(APPLAUSE)</font>

58:28.630 --> 58:29.847
<font color="#D900D9">(CHEERING)</font>

58:29.965 --> 58:30.966
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font>

58:32.217 --> 58:34.219
This could be a lot of bites.

58:52.320 --> 58:53.742
I'm so hot.

58:57.659 --> 59:01.334
Okay, everybody! Joyce has got
25 minutes to go now!

59:01.663 --> 59:03.256
Watch the clock!

59:11.339 --> 59:13.182
Excuse me. Sorry.

59:13.508 --> 59:15.055
- I'm sorry.
- It's okay. <font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

59:16.344 --> 59:18.346
I've seen all sorts of people
get after that steak,

59:18.430 --> 59:19.682
but never one like that.

59:22.184 --> 59:23.857
That's, uh, my mom.

59:25.854 --> 59:26.855
That's your mom?

59:27.105 --> 59:28.948
I would not lie about that, no.
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font>

59:29.608 --> 59:31.451
I'm Benjamin Graw.
My friends call me Ben.

59:32.194 --> 59:33.411
Hi, Ben Graw.

59:33.487 --> 59:37.037
I'm Andrew Brewster.
My mother calls me Andy.

59:37.282 --> 59:39.205
What brings you to Lubbock, Andy?

59:39.701 --> 59:42.295
<font color="#D900D9">(STAMMERING)</font> I'm traveling for work.

59:42.370 --> 59:43.650
I'm just passing through, kinda.

59:43.705 --> 59:46.049
Yeah, me, too. I'm headed to Tulsa.

59:46.374 --> 59:48.217
I always try and make
a stop here on my way,

59:48.543 --> 59:49.795
you know, at the Steak Ranch here,

59:49.878 --> 59:52.097
watching people get
physically ill onstage.

59:52.172 --> 59:53.765
It just don't get
much more American than that.

59:53.840 --> 59:54.841
It doesn't, no.

59:55.300 --> 59:57.894
No, no. She should
save the shrimp for last.

59:58.386 --> 01:00:00.013
I'm kind of an expert by now.

01:00:00.097 --> 01:00:02.065
I could help your mom,
give her some tips.

01:00:03.725 --> 01:00:05.568
Yeah! Sure. Why not?

01:00:05.644 --> 01:00:07.237
- Go for it. Yeah.
- Okay.

01:00:13.068 --> 01:00:15.366
Howdy, ma'am. Your son, Andrew,

01:00:15.445 --> 01:00:17.413
said I should come over
and give you a hand.

01:00:17.739 --> 01:00:20.208
See, the key is the size
of the pieces you cut off,

01:00:20.283 --> 01:00:21.803
- you gotta keep them small.
- Mmm-hmm.

01:00:22.869 --> 01:00:23.870
One other thing.

01:00:25.413 --> 01:00:27.336
What? What is it?

01:00:27.415 --> 01:00:29.258
It's called the cycle.

01:00:29.334 --> 01:00:31.454
You got to learn the cycle,
which is two small pieces,

01:00:31.753 --> 01:00:34.632
potato, salad, then you have
two small pieces of steak,

01:00:34.714 --> 01:00:36.091
- potato, salad.
- About that size?

01:00:36.174 --> 01:00:37.767
Yeah. That's perfect, actually.

01:00:37.843 --> 01:00:39.516
You'll get that down a lot faster.

01:00:39.761 --> 01:00:41.763
- Okay. So two of those...
- Two of those.

01:00:42.013 --> 01:00:43.014
There you go.

01:00:43.098 --> 01:00:44.691
I wish I could offer you some but I can't.

01:00:44.766 --> 01:00:46.018
No, you got to eat this all yourself.

01:00:46.101 --> 01:00:47.273
- And then that.
- Yeah.

01:00:48.270 --> 01:00:50.364
- That's perfect.
- Is that good?

01:00:50.438 --> 01:00:53.567
Yeah, it's good. You actually
did all four at the same time.

01:00:53.650 --> 01:00:55.690
That's pretty good.
Now let's keep going. <font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

01:00:56.611 --> 01:00:58.613
Mom's talking to a cowboy.

01:00:58.947 --> 01:01:00.949
<font color="#808080">EMCEE:</font> Come on!
It's four minutes to go for Joyce!

01:01:01.074 --> 01:01:03.042
Give her a hand. Get up and
give her some encouragement!

01:01:03.118 --> 01:01:06.793
- Faster, Andy, cut faster!
- I'm going as fast as I can.

01:01:07.455 --> 01:01:08.798
My arm's falling off.

01:01:09.040 --> 01:01:10.383
Is it hot in here, or...

01:01:10.625 --> 01:01:12.548
It's actually really, really hot in here.

01:01:12.627 --> 01:01:13.924
It's not just you this time. <font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

01:01:14.045 --> 01:01:16.343
You think I could ask them
for a little ketchup?

01:01:16.423 --> 01:01:18.016
I think you could ask
for whatever you want, Mom.

01:01:18.133 --> 01:01:19.225
I'll get you some ketchup.

01:01:19.301 --> 01:01:20.302
But I'd like a little seltzer, too.

01:01:20.385 --> 01:01:22.137
No, no. No seltzer, you need flat water.

01:01:22.220 --> 01:01:23.472
Seltzer will make you too full.

01:01:23.555 --> 01:01:25.075
- Where's the ketchup?
- Are you okay?

01:01:25.307 --> 01:01:26.980
- No, I'm not okay.
- Are you sure?

01:01:27.225 --> 01:01:28.226
I'm not okay!

01:01:28.393 --> 01:01:29.986
You know what?
You know what? Look...

01:01:30.061 --> 01:01:31.313
- I'm throwing in the towel.
- I wanted to do this.

01:01:31.396 --> 01:01:32.739
No, I'm throwing it in.

01:01:32.981 --> 01:01:34.574
Andy, I don't want you
to have to pay 100 bucks

01:01:34.649 --> 01:01:35.650
- for a lousy piece of meat!
- It's fine!

01:01:35.734 --> 01:01:37.281
Honestly, I'd rather pay 1,000 bucks

01:01:37.360 --> 01:01:38.407
than watch you vomit
in front of these people!

01:01:38.653 --> 01:01:40.075
Hold on. Hold on. Ride it out.

01:01:40.322 --> 01:01:41.539
All right? I want you to
take a sip of water,

01:01:41.615 --> 01:01:42.616
I want you to think happy thoughts.

01:01:42.699 --> 01:01:43.700
What makes you happy?

01:01:43.992 --> 01:01:45.164
Eating.

01:01:45.660 --> 01:01:47.333
That actually helps a little bit.

01:01:47.579 --> 01:01:49.820
But I don't know what to do now!
I don't know what to do.

01:01:49.831 --> 01:01:52.584
You're going to finish!
Come on, let's go! Finish!

01:01:52.667 --> 01:01:53.793
Finish!

01:01:53.877 --> 01:01:55.595
- Come on!
- Okay.

01:01:55.670 --> 01:01:57.843
- Yes! Steak! Come on!
<font color="#D900D9">(CHEERING)</font>

01:01:58.173 --> 01:02:00.392
Okay, everybody, come here!

01:02:00.467 --> 01:02:02.845
I think she's going to do it!
Come on! Let's go!

01:02:03.678 --> 01:02:05.772
And over there. Come on!

01:02:05.889 --> 01:02:07.641
<font color="#D900D9">(APPLAUSE AND CHEERING)</font>

01:02:10.352 --> 01:02:12.195
Yes! The steak's gone!

01:02:15.106 --> 01:02:16.949
You gotta shoot it! Shoot it like a shot.

01:02:17.192 --> 01:02:18.660
Shoot it? What's a "shoot it"?

01:02:18.735 --> 01:02:19.736
- Like a shot!
- Like this, you go like...

01:02:19.861 --> 01:02:22.865
Oh, you mean like in the movies!

01:02:24.532 --> 01:02:26.205
Ladies and gentlemen,

01:02:26.868 --> 01:02:29.371
- this is to my son.<font color="#808080">
CROWD:</font> - Aw!

01:02:29.704 --> 01:02:31.065
And don't forget the free T-shirt.

01:02:31.122 --> 01:02:32.715
- I won't.
- Shoot it!

01:02:35.794 --> 01:02:37.546
<font color="#D900D9">(BELL DINGS)</font>

01:02:37.837 --> 01:02:39.714
<font color="#D900D9">(WILD CHEERING)</font>

01:02:40.799 --> 01:02:42.392
<font color="#D900D9">(WHOOPING)</font>

01:02:42.509 --> 01:02:43.977
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font>

01:02:44.302 --> 01:02:45.303
Yeah!

01:02:45.553 --> 01:02:46.645
Thank you, honey.

01:02:48.265 --> 01:02:49.482
Mmm.

01:02:49.891 --> 01:02:51.452
So, you going to do
any more sightseeing

01:02:51.518 --> 01:02:52.895
on the rest of your trip?

01:02:52.978 --> 01:02:54.070
<font color="#808080">BOTH:</font> Um...

01:02:54.396 --> 01:02:55.488
We wish we could.

01:02:55.563 --> 01:02:57.565
We're actually
on a pretty tight schedule.

01:02:57.816 --> 01:03:00.490
We're going to Santa Fe, Las Vegas,
and then San Francisco.

01:03:00.735 --> 01:03:03.409
Well, I do hope you get to
stop at the Grand Canyon.

01:03:03.738 --> 01:03:05.581
Oh, no, we can't this time

01:03:05.657 --> 01:03:08.080
because we're really
on a very tight schedule.

01:03:08.410 --> 01:03:10.913
- Well, maybe next trip, then.
- Yeah.

01:03:12.247 --> 01:03:14.249
Andrew. It was a pleasure.

01:03:14.499 --> 01:03:16.672
Oh, yeah. You, too. Thank you so much.

01:03:16.918 --> 01:03:18.591
And thank you.
Thank you very, very much.

01:03:18.920 --> 01:03:21.093
Thank you. And could I have
a second with your mom?

01:03:21.589 --> 01:03:24.934
Yeah! For sure. Yeah. Thanks.

01:03:25.260 --> 01:03:27.763
I hope this isn't being too forward,

01:03:28.013 --> 01:03:30.892
but when I see a woman eat like that,

01:03:30.974 --> 01:03:33.054
well, it just makes a man
want to stick his neck out.

01:03:33.351 --> 01:03:34.523
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

01:03:34.602 --> 01:03:36.195
I do business in New York.

01:03:36.604 --> 01:03:37.730
I was hoping maybe I could

01:03:37.814 --> 01:03:39.135
take you out to dinner one night.

01:03:40.191 --> 01:03:41.192
Hmm.

01:03:41.276 --> 01:03:42.448
I do know some restaurants

01:03:42.527 --> 01:03:44.120
where you don't have to eat on a stage.

01:03:44.195 --> 01:03:45.492
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font>

01:03:46.281 --> 01:03:47.954
That's funny.

01:03:50.118 --> 01:03:53.793
The thing about dating...
It is a date, right?

01:03:54.414 --> 01:03:55.666
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

01:03:55.790 --> 01:03:58.964
It's just so uncomfortable,

01:03:59.294 --> 01:04:02.218
talking and eating
with someone you don't know.

01:04:02.464 --> 01:04:04.137
Some would argue that
that's actually how

01:04:04.215 --> 01:04:05.307
you get to know someone.

01:04:06.301 --> 01:04:08.975
Yeah, that's... You could argue that.

01:04:09.596 --> 01:04:10.939
<font color="#D900D9">(JOYCE STAMMERS)</font>

01:04:11.139 --> 01:04:13.983
I don't know what to say.
It's just been a long time.

01:04:14.309 --> 01:04:16.482
Well, I tell you what.

01:04:17.479 --> 01:04:18.822
When you're ready,

01:04:19.981 --> 01:04:21.324
give me a call.

01:04:22.484 --> 01:04:24.452
I will think about it, Ben.

01:04:25.653 --> 01:04:26.996
Joyce.

01:04:30.325 --> 01:04:32.999
- Drive carefully!
- I will. You take care now.

01:04:33.328 --> 01:04:34.750
Bye, Mr. Graw! Nice to meet you.

01:04:34.829 --> 01:04:35.830
- It's Ben. Ben.
- See you, Andrew.

01:04:35.914 --> 01:04:37.757
- Bye, Ben!
<font color="#D900D9">(ENGINE STARTS)</font>

01:04:37.832 --> 01:04:41.006
- How scandalous! Mother!
- Don't you say...

01:04:41.336 --> 01:04:42.337
What a scandal!

01:04:42.670 --> 01:04:44.513
Stop it. Come on. Don't do that.

01:04:44.839 --> 01:04:46.682
"I'll think about it, Ben."

01:04:46.925 --> 01:04:47.972
- That's exactly...
- That's so...

01:04:48.051 --> 01:04:49.223
You're blushing right now,
you know that?

01:04:49.302 --> 01:04:51.302
- That is so nasty!
- That's exactly what you said.

01:04:51.346 --> 01:04:53.519
You know, he's very nice. God!

01:04:53.848 --> 01:04:57.193
I haven't had that much fun
in such a long time. You know?

01:04:57.519 --> 01:04:58.611
Maybe you're right, Andy.

01:04:58.686 --> 01:05:01.030
Maybe I need a little more
adventure in my life.

01:05:01.356 --> 01:05:03.700
I'm really tired of going to the Gap.

01:05:04.025 --> 01:05:06.244
- Are you actually?
- No. Actually, I'm not.

01:05:06.319 --> 01:05:07.445
<font color="#D900D9">(BOTH CHUCKLE)</font>

01:05:07.612 --> 01:05:09.614
It's just that I'm a grown woman

01:05:09.864 --> 01:05:14.210
and the most exciting place
I've ever been is Florida.

